===尚未全國性生效===
*{{MEX}}：2015年{{Internal link helper/en|墨西哥最高法院|New Mexico Supreme Court|最高法院}}裁決，任何將婚姻限於只能異性之間登記的州法律都帶有歧視性已經[[違憲審查|違憲]]，各州必須完成同性婚姻法制化的修法。至2022年6月，全國有[[墨西哥城|墨西哥城]]及其他27個州全境、1個州境内部分地區施行同性婚姻。<ref>{{Cite web|title=墨西哥索諾拉州通過「同婚合法」 全國已約3/4區域SAY YES - 國際|url=https://news.ltn.com.tw/news/world/breakingnews/3682146|access-date=2021-10-03|date=2021-09-24|last=自由時報電子報|work=自由時報電子報|language=zh-TW|archive-date=2021-12-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211213061621/https://news.ltn.com.tw/news/world/breakingnews/3682146|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Agren_2010">{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/08/11/world/americas/11mexico.html|title=Mexican States Ordered to Honor Gay Marriages|accessdate=2019-04-21|date=2010-10-10|publisher=紐約時報|last=大衛|first=艾倫|format=html|language=en|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100812141124/https://www.nytimes.com/2010/08/11/world/americas/11mexico.html|archivedate=2010-08-12|dead-url=no|quote=MEXICO CITY — The Mexican Supreme Court ruled Tuesday that each of the country’s 31 states must recognize same-sex marriages registered in Mexico City, potentially giving gay and lesbian couples full matrimonial rights nationwide.The court had already ruled this month that Mexico City’s same-sex marriage law, which took effect in March and has resulted in hundreds of same-sex marriages, was constitutional.While the court made it clear that state governments were not obligated to enact same-sex marriage laws of their own, it did require them to recognize the legality of such marriages performed in Mexico City.}}</ref>

