|| [[墨西哥同性婚姻|墨西哥同性婚姻]]，2015年，最高法院下令同性伴侶可向當地法院申請強制令，要求禁止的州發給結婚證書，被認為是技術性地達成全國通過，不過有些州在法令上的限制仍未變動<ref>{{cite news|title=Mexican Supreme Court clears way for same sex marriage in all 32 states|url=http://www.theyucatantimes.com/2016/01/unanimous-supreme-court-ruling-clears-way-for-same-sex-marriage-in-all-32-states/|agency=Yucatan Times|date=2016-01-29|quote=Same-sex marriage was already legal in Mexico City, Chihuahua, Coahuila, Nayarit and Quintana Roo. All Mexican states must already recognize the legality of same-sex marriages performed in those states whether or not their state performs same-sex marriages yet because of a prior Supreme Court ruling.|access-date=2016-04-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160330213841/http://www.theyucatantimes.com/2016/01/unanimous-supreme-court-ruling-clears-way-for-same-sex-marriage-in-all-32-states/|archive-date=2016-03-30|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=How Mexico Quietly Legalized Same-Sex Marriage|url=http://www.npr.org/sections/parallels/2015/06/16/414964843/how-mexico-quietly-legalized-same-sex-marriage|agency=NPR|date=2015-06-16|quote=Couples denied marriage licenses can now directly appeal to local judges who will be bound by the Supreme Court ruling and must force local clerks to issue the license.|access-date=2016-04-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160325200936/http://www.npr.org/sections/parallels/2015/06/16/414964843/how-mexico-quietly-legalized-same-sex-marriage|archive-date=2016-03-25|dead-url=no}}</ref>
